From 75bad00959b3b9676fa2d727ef597817e720d695 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: dylanyunlon <dylanyunlong@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 20 May 2026 04:20:54 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] M421-M435: Enable 13B LOC+SP training on heterogeneous 3-GPU
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Following CCCL f984c90 (Extract first histogram-only pass in DeviceTopK
into its own kernel), this commit restructures the training pipeline to
support 13B (n_layer=40, n_head=40, n_embd=5120) on 2xA6000+1xH100.

7 files changed, +240 -128 lines. Zero new files.

=== Problem chain discovered through production debugging ===

  1. deepspeed/ops/adam/__init__.py imported DESLOCFusedAdam (never
     implemented in M058) -> import deepspeed raised ImportError ->
     except Exception silently set _DS_AVAILABLE=False -> every DESLOC
     run fell through to _train_baseline (no DeepSpeed engine, no
     cpu_offload, no ZeRO) -> OOM on 13B.

  2. GPT().to(device) moved fp32 model (50.4GB) to A6000 (47.5GB)
     before bf16 conversion -> OOM during model loading.

  3. ds_config had fp16.enabled=True -> FP16_UnfusedOptimizer cloned
     fp32 master weights on GPU (51.4GB for 13B) -> OOM.

  4. ZeRO stage 0 ignores offload_optimizer config. ZeRO stage 1
     partitions optimizer states only, not gradients. 13B bf16
     params(25.7GB) + full grads(25.7GB) = 51.4GB > 47.5GB -> OOM.

  5. DeslocProgress(max_steps) but constructor takes no args -> TypeError.

  6. engine.compile(backend=inductor) requires PyTorch >= 2.9 but ags1
     has 2.7.1 -> AutoSP compile failed -> SP disabled entirely instead
     of falling back to eager Ulysses.

=== Fixes (all in existing files, zero new files) ===

deepspeed/ops/adam/__init__.py:
  - Remove broken DESLOCFusedAdam/DESLOCCPUAdam import lines

REAL_GPU_BENCHMARK.py (+120 -17):
  - Print DeepSpeed import error with traceback instead of silent except
  - Construct model on CPU, convert bf16, then .to(device)
  - Switch ds_config from fp16 to bf16 mode
  - Auto-escalate ZeRO: 7B/13B + cpu_offload -> stage 2 + offload_param
  - Allow --zero_stage 2 in argparse
  - Fix DeslocProgress() call (no args)
  - When engine.compile fails (PyTorch <2.9), fall back to eager Ulysses:
    probe GPU types, group same-type ranks, create SP group (sp_size=2
    on ags1: 2xA6000, n_heads=40, 40%2=0), H100 stays DP-only
  - Scatter input_ids/labels along seq dim in DeepSpeed training loop
    when eager SP is active

csrc/includes/deepcompile.h (+43):
  - Add sp_group_id_ field to DSParam with accessors
  - Add sp_comm_, sp_size_, kx_, warmup_steps_, step_ to CustomOpExecutor
  - Add shouldSyncDP() for Kx warmup gating
  - Extract flushSPReduceBucket() from flushReduceBucket (mirrors CCCL
    extracting invoke_histogram_only from filter_and_histogram)

csrc/compile/z1.cpp (+75 -2):
  - Restructure flushReduceBucket: call flushSPReduceBucket first (SP
    params every step), then Kx-gate DP AllReduce (skip non-SP params
    on non-boundary steps). Mirrors CCCL dispatch loop: pass-0 uses
    dedicated histogram kernel, loop starts at pass=1.
  - Add endBackward() override to increment step_ for Kx ramp
  - Add register_graph_z1_sp with NCCL communicator init for SP group
  - Add register_param_sp with sp_group_id assignment

csrc/compile/z1.h (+11):
  - Declare register_graph_z1_sp and register_param_sp

csrc/compile/init.cpp (+4):
  - Register register_graph_z1_sp and register_param_sp in pybind11

run_experiment_13b_locsp.sh (rewritten):
  - All phases use DESLOC (not DDP — DDP baseline infeasible on A6000)
  - Kx=1 serves as DDP-equivalent baseline
  - batch_size=1, grad_accum=8 throughout
  - All phases use --cpu_offload --use_ac --use_autosp

=== Predicted issues for next debugging session ===

  P1. ZeRO-2 + DES-LOC Kx gating: engine.py allreduce_gradients checks
      zero_optimization_stage() < 1 for Kx skip. With stage=2 this is
      always False, so Kx gating never fires. For Kx=1 baseline this is
      correct (every-step sync). For Kx=32 experiments, the engine.py
      check needs to be relaxed or DES-LOC must gate at a different level.

  P2. ZeRO-2 offload_param + bf16: DeepSpeed ZeRO-2 with param offload
      may trigger parameter gathering before forward. If the model was
      already .to(device) with full params, this double-loads. Monitor
      GPU memory at step 1.

  P3. Eager Ulysses in _train_deepspeed: the scatter happens at the
      Python level but engine.backward() runs ZeRO-2 gradient reduction
      which expects full-sequence gradients. The SP A2A inside attention
      reconstructs full-head context, so backward gradients should be
      correctly shaped. But if ZeRO-2 reduce_scatter partitions gradients
      before the reverse A2A completes, shapes may mismatch. Watch for
      NCCL errors at step 1 backward.

  P4. engine.py line 366 warning about ZeRO stage != 0: this is a
      warning only, not a hard error. Training proceeds but the warning
      is expected.

=== User-perspective critique ===

  U1. 7B experiments that previously ran with --use_autosp will now get
      ZeRO-2 auto-escalation (7B is in the large_model list). This
      changes their optimizer path from BF16_Optimizer to ZeRO-2
      stage_1_and_2.py. Loss curves may differ from previous runs.
      Mitigation: user can pass --zero_stage 0 explicitly to override.

  U2. The bf16 ds_config change affects all model sizes, not just 13B.
      Small models (125M, 700M) that previously used fp16 with loss
      scaling now use bf16 without scaling. Numerically different.
      Mitigation: bf16 has same dynamic range as fp32 (8 exponent bits),
      so convergence should be equivalent or better.

=== System-perspective critique ===

  S1. The eager Ulysses fallback in _train_deepspeed duplicates 60 lines
      of GPU-probing logic from _train_baseline __init__. Should be
      factored into a shared _init_eager_sp() method. Deferred to avoid
      touching _train_baseline which is known-working for 7B.

  S2. register_graph_z1_sp creates a new NCCL communicator via
      ncclCommInitRank. If called multiple times (e.g., torch.compile
      retracing), this leaks communicators. The if(sp_size>1) guard
      prevents double-init but does not handle cleanup. Production
      deployment needs ncclCommDestroy in the cleanup() path.

  S3. The ZeRO-2 auto-escalation uses config.model_size string matching
      ('7B', '13B'). A model named '6.7B' would not trigger escalation.
      Should use parameter count threshold instead, but _build_ds_config
      has no self (static-like method). Deferred.

Signed-off-by: dylanyunlon <dylanyunlong@gmail.com>
